		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: 8x16 and whatever else unreg wants to know</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Essentially the CPU does this when you power it on:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; sei<br />&nbsp; jmp ($FFFC)</div><br />So if the vector at $FFFC points to your reset handler, then yes, it'll start at the beginning of your reset handler.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


